Presentation of the problem¶

Sales fees: Olist takes a 10% cut on the product price (excl. freight) of each order delivered

Subscription fees: Olist charges 80 BRL by month per seller

Cost of reviews:

1 star : 100 BRL

2 stars : 50 BRL

3 stars : 40 BRL

4 and 5 stars : 0 BRL

IT Costs : Depends on the number of sellers and the quantity of products

from olist.seller import Seller

sellers = Seller().get_training_data()
sellers = sellers.copy()

sellers["revenues"] = 0.1*sellers["sales"] + 80*sellers["months_on_olist"]


from olist.data import Olist
from olist.order import Order
olist = Olist()
data = olist.get_data()
seller_df = Order().get_review_score()

reviews_cost = {1: 100,
2: 50,
3: 40,
4: 0,
5: 0}

merged_df = seller_df.merge(data["order_items"], on = "order_id")
merged_df["cost_of_reviews"] = merged_df["review_score"].map(reviews_cost)
merged_df = merged_df.groupby("seller_id")[["cost_of_reviews"]].sum().reset_index()
merged_df

sellers = sellers.merge(merged_df, on = "seller_id")

sellers["profits"] = sellers["revenues"] - sellers["cost_of_reviews"]

alpha = 3157.27
beta = 978.23
n_sellers = sellers["seller_id"].nunique()
n_products = sellers["quantity"].sum()
IT_costs = alpha*(n_sellers**0.5) + beta*(n_products**0.5)
round(IT_costs, 2)

sellers = sellers.sort_values(by = "profits")

initial_global_profit = sellers["profits"].sum()
new_global_profit = initial_global_profit
financial_impact = []
removed_sellers = []
for i in range(len(sellers)): 
    seller_profit = sellers.iloc[i]['profits']
    new_global_profit -= seller_profit
    new_global_profit = round(new_global_profit, 2)
    financial_impact.append(new_global_profit)
    removed_sellers.append(i+1)
sellers["financial_impact"] = financial_impact
sellers["removed_sellers"] = removed_sellers

initial__IT_costs = 500000
new_IT_costs = 0
IT_costs = []
quantity_removed = []
new_quantity = sellers["quantity"].sum()
for i in range(len(sellers)): 
    quantity = sellers.iloc[i]['quantity']
    new_quantity -= quantity
    new_IT_costs = alpha*((len(sellers) - i)**0.5) + beta*(new_quantity**0.5)
    IT_costs.append(new_IT_costs)
    quantity_removed.append(new_quantity)
sellers["IT_costs"] = IT_costs
sellers["quantity_removed"] = quantity_removed

sellers["net_profits"] = sellers["financial_impact"] - sellers["IT_costs"]
net_profits = list(sellers["net_profits"])
sellers["net_profits"].idxmax()

max_profit_index = sellers["financial_impact"].idxmax()
n_removed_sellers = sellers.loc[max_profit_index ]["removed_sellers"]
max_net_profit_index = sellers["net_profits"].idxmax()
n_removed_seller_nets = sellers.loc[max_net_profit_index]["removed_sellers"]

maximum = "{:,.1f}".format(max(sellers["financial_impact"]))
plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
plt.plot( sellers["removed_sellers"], sellers["financial_impact"], label = "profits per removed sellers")
plt.xlabel("number of removed sellers")
#plt.ylabel("global profits")
max_index = financial_impact.index(max(financial_impact))

plt.scatter(removed_sellers[max_index], financial_impact[max_index], color='red')
plt.annotate(f"max profits : {maximum} for {n_removed_sellers} removed sellers",
             xy=(removed_sellers[max_index], financial_impact[max_index]),
             xytext=(removed_sellers[max_index] + 100, financial_impact[max_index] - 50))

plt.plot(sellers["removed_sellers"], sellers["IT_costs"], label = "IT_costs per removed sellers")
maximum2 = "{:,.1f}".format(max(sellers["net_profits"]))
max_index_net = net_profits.index(max(net_profits))
plt.scatter(removed_sellers[max_index_net], net_profits[max_index_net], color='red')
plt.annotate(f"max profits : {maximum2} for {n_removed_seller_nets} removed sellers",
             xy=(removed_sellers[max_index_net], net_profits[max_index_net]),
             xytext=(removed_sellers[max_index_net] + 100, net_profits[max_index_net] - 50))


plt.plot(sellers["removed_sellers"] ,sellers["net_profits"], label = "net_profits")
plt.grid()
plt.legend()
plt.title ("profits vs seller removed")
Out[3]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'profits vs seller removed')

removing sellers
